body:
@bluebill1049  so by continuing to dig I narrowed this down to what seems to be a persistent issue around `mode: onBlur` and required radio inputs.  Making the radio inputs not required solves the issue, or changing `mode` to `onChange`.

I had opened a similar issue before on this topic, never got around to trying to contribute a fix.  For now my work around was the following: 

Ensure only one of each named radio inputs has `ref={register({ required: true })}`
On each of the radio inputs add an `onChange` handler with the following function:

```
function onRadioChange(e) {
  trigger(e.target.name);
}
```

This causes the radio inputs to successfully register as having a value.  `mode: 'onBlur'` simply does not work out of the box with required radio inputs
